The characteristics of cloud computing, as defined by the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST), include:


 -  On-demand self-service, which allows users to provision and deploy computing resources as needed without human interaction;


 -  Broad network access, which allows users to access cloud services over the internet using a variety of devices;


 -  Resource pooling, which allows cloud providers to share computing resources among multiple users, improving efficiency and reducing costs;


 -  Rapid elasticity, which allows cloud services to be quickly and easily scaled up or down to meet changing demand;


 -  Measured service, which allows cloud providers to monitor and measure the use of computing resources and charge users based on their actual usage.


 These characteristics enable cloud computing to provide a flexible, scalable, and cost-effective way to access and use computing resources.
